\end{itemize}

\subsection{Post-C1 dependency note}

After the Phase~C1 refactor (iter-109), $\mathrm{LineBundle}\,X$ is the units of the skeleton of the symmetric monoidal category $X.\mathrm{Modules}$ (Chapter~\ref{chap:Picard_LineBundle}), matching the geometric definition of "invertible quasi-coherent $\mathcal O_X$-module modulo isomorphism" on schemes of every shape. The global-sections-approximation caveat that previously qualified $\PicardFunctor$ on non-affine $S$ is therefore no longer in force; the $\PicardFunctor(S)$ values are now isomorphism classes of invertible $\mathcal O_{C \times_k S}$-modules in the correct sense.

The $\PicardFunctor$ construction nonetheless transitively consumes two named-deferred sorries, both surfaced in Chapter~\ref{chap:Picard_LineBundle}.

\begin{itemize}
  \item \emph{Pull-back gap.} The Lean body of $\mathrm{Pic.pullback}$ (\texttt{AlgebraicJacobian/Picard/LineBundle.lean:93}) is currently \texttt{sorry}, pending closure of (or a hand-construction equivalent to) Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_tensorObj} (\texttt{Picard/LineBundle.lean:82}): the monoidality iso $f^*(M \otimes_{\mathcal O_Y} N) \cong f^* M \otimes_{\mathcal O_X} f^* N$ of the categorical pull-back functor $\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullback}\,f$ on quasi-coherent $\mathcal O$-modules. The functoriality lemmas $\mathrm{Pic.pullback\_id}$ and $\mathrm{Pic.pullback\_comp}$ (\texttt{Picard/LineBundle.lean:99,\,105}) are likewise sorry-bodied for the same reason. Definition~\ref{def:Pic_functor} consumes the pull-back via the projection subgroup $p_S^*\Pic(S)$, and Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_Pic_pullback} packages the dependency. The well-definedness of $\mathrm{PicardFunctor.quotMap}$ (descent of $\mathrm{Pic.pullback}\,(\mathrm{fiberMap}\,C\,f)$ through $\mathrm{QuotientGroup.lift}$) compiles because it reasons against the \emph{statements} of $\mathrm{Pic.pullback\_id}$ and $\mathrm{Pic.pullback\_comp}$ rather than against their computational unfolding.
  \item \emph{Monoidality-of-sheafification gap.} The $\mathrm{CommGroup}\,(\Pic(X))$ structure derives from $\mathrm{BraidedCategory}\,(X.\mathrm{Modules})$ through the localization-monoidal chain, which transitively requires $(W\,X).\mathrm{IsMonoidal}$ --- the project's $\mathrm{instIsMonoidal\_W}$ (\texttt{AlgebraicJacobian/Modules/Monoidal.lean:166}). See Chapter~\ref{chap:Picard_LineBundle}'s load-bearing-disclosure paragraph and Chapter~\ref{chap:Modules_Monoidal}.
\end{itemize}

Consequently, \texttt{lean\_verify} on $\PicardFunctor$ and on $\mathrm{PicardFunctor.quotMap}$ exposes \texttt{sorryAx} chains rooted at \texttt{Picard/LineBundle.lean:93,\,82} (the pull-back chain) and, indirectly, at \texttt{Modules/Monoidal.lean:166} (the monoidality-of-sheafification chain). The same chains propagate to $\PicardFunctorAb$ (Chapter~\ref{chap:Picard_FunctorAb}) and through to the Jacobian arc. The representability theorem stated above (Theorem~\ref{thm:Pic_representable}) remains deferred under the Phase~C3 exit policy and is separately downstream of these C1/C2 sorries.

